{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"0434d367-c6b7-482c-8ca7-37c5165ef1eb","agentId":"a350bc1c9d32f0cbc","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are implementing Task 1: Database Schema\n\n## Task Description\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `database/schema.sql`\n\n**Step 1: Create schema file**\n\n```sql\n-- database/schema.sql\n-- Run as superuser:  psql -U postgres -f database/schema.sql\n\nCREATE DATABASE xsalto_fidelity;\n\n\\c xsalto_fidelity;\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS contacts (\n    id          VARCHAR(50)  PRIMARY KEY,\n    lastname    VARCHAR(255),\n    firstname   VARCHAR(255),\n    email       VARCHAR(255),\n    address1    VARCHAR(255),\n    address2    VARCHAR(255),\n    address3    VARCHAR(255),\n    zipcode     VARCHAR(20),\n    city        VARCHAR(255),\n    country     VARCHAR(10),\n    balance     INTEGER,\n    lastmove    TIMESTAMP,\n    language    VARCHAR(10),\n    skiers      JSONB,\n    resorts     JSONB,\n    created     TIMESTAMP\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS pages (\n    offset       INTEGER      PRIMARY KEY,\n    size         INTEGER      NOT NULL DEFAULT 100,\n    downloaded_at TIMESTAMP   NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n    record_count INTEGER,\n    status       VARCHAR(20)  NOT NULL DEFAULT 'completed'\n);\n```\n\n**Step 2: Initialize git repo and commit**\n\n```bash\ngit init\ngit add database/schema.sql\ngit commit -m \"feat: add postgresql schema for contacts and pages tables\"\n```\n\n## Context\n\nThis is a greenfield PHP project. The working directory `/home/xav/Workspace/ElibertyRepos/xsalto-pds-fid` is NOT yet a git repository. You need to:\n1. Initialize git (`git init`)\n2. Create the `database/` directory\n3. Write the schema SQL file\n4. Stage and commit it\n\nThe schema serves a PHP API importer that pulls contacts from the Xsalto PDS API and stores them in PostgreSQL. The `contacts` table holds contact records; the `pages` table tracks which API pages have been downloaded (for retry/resume).\n\nNote: `offset` is a reserved word in PostgreSQL but is valid as a column name when quoted if needed. As a primary key column name it works fine unquoted in PostgreSQL.\n\n## Your Job\n\n1. Run `git init` in `/home/xav/Workspace/ElibertyRepos/xsalto-pds-fid`\n2. Create `database/schema.sql` with the exact content above\n3. Commit it\n4. Self-review and report back\n\nWork from: `/home/xav/Workspace/ElibertyRepos/xsalto-pds-fid`\n\n## Report Format\n\n- **Status:** DONE | DONE_WITH_CONCERNS | BLOCKED | NEEDS_CONTEXT\n- What you implemented\n- Files changed\n- Self-review findings\n"},"uuid":"31555ace-4947-4272-8e46-f38953836f78","timestamp":"2026-03-31T09:24:55.237Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/xav/Workspace/ElibertyRepos/xsalto-pds-fid","sessionId":"7adf6774-7b0d-45b6-aa96-f0c904ea4708","version":"2.1.85","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"compiled-riding-pinwheel"}
